        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 24 at 8:10AM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>Patchy, dense fog has developed across parts of the Lower Hudson
Valley and interior southern Connecticut this morning. Fog is
mainly in river valleys.

Visibility may be reduced to below a quarter mile, in spots. Fog
is expected to clear over the next few hours.

Motorists within these locations this morning should proceed with
extra caution and be prepared for rapid changes in visibility. Use
low beam headlights and allow for extra space between vehicles.
</description>
